[[Category:Lines of longitude|w003 meridian west]]

{{Location map-line|lat=70}}
{{kml}}
[[File:VictoriaIslandMap.png|thumb|right|On [[Victoria Island (Canada)|Victoria Island]], [[Canada]], part of the border between [[Northwest Territories]] (green) and [[Nunavut]] (white) is defined by the 70th parallel north]]
The '''70th parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 70 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]], in the [[Arctic]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[North America]], and passes through some of the southern seas of the [[Arctic Ocean]].

At this latitude the [[sun]] is visible for 24 hours, 0 minutes during the [[summer solstice]] and Civil Twilight during the [[winter solstice]].

