{{Marine-current-stub}}

'''Georg Cornelius Karl Gerland''' (29 January 1833, in [[Kassel]] &ndash; 16 February 1919, in [[Strasbourg]]) was a German [[anthropologist]] and [[geophysicist]].
He studied [[classical philology]], [[German studies|Germanistics]] and anthropology at the universities of [[University of Berlin|Berlin]] and [[University of Marburg|Marburg]].<ref>[https://www.deutsche-biographie.de/sfz69899.html#ndbcontent Gerland, Georg Cornelius Karl] In: [[Neue Deutsche Biographie]]</ref> From 1856 to 1875 he successively worked as a gymnasium teacher in Kassel, [[Hanau]], [[Magdeburg]] and [[Halle an der Saale]], and in 1875 was named a professor of [[ethnology]] and [[geography]] at the [[University of Strasbourg]]. In 1900 he became director of the Imperial Central Bureau for Earthquake Research in Strasbourg.<ref>[http://www.lagis-hessen.de/pnd/116587938 Gerland, Karl Cornelius Georg] Hessian Biography</ref>
== Published works == From 1887 onward, he edited the ''Beiträge zur Geophysik'', a journal of geophysics eventually known as ''Gerlands Beiträge zur Geophysik''.<ref>[https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000640798 Gerlands Beiträge zur Geophysik] HathiTrust Digital Library]</ref> After the death of [[Theodor Waitz]], he edited and published the last two volumes of Waitz's ''Die Anthropologie der Naturvölker'' (6 volumes, 1859–65).<ref>[https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_American_Cyclop%C3%A6dia_(1879)/Waitz,_Theodor The American Cyclopædia (1879)/Waitz, Theodor]</ref><ref>[https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001878784 Anthropologie der naturvölker] HathiTrust Digital Library</ref> In addition, he was the author of a handful of biographies in the ''[[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]''.<ref>[https://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Kategorie:ADB:Autor:Otto_Gerland Kategorie:ADB:Autor:Otto Gerland] In: [[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]</ref> Other written efforts by Gerland include: * ''Der altgriechische Dativ, zunächst des Singularis'', 1859 &ndash; The ancient Greek dative. * ''Ueber Goethe's historische Stellung; eine Abhandlung'', 1865 &ndash; On [[Goethe]]'s historical position. * ''Altgriechische märchen in der Odyssee, ein beitrag zur vergleichenden mythologie'', 1869 &ndash; Ancient Greek fairy tale in the ''[[Odyssey]]''. * ''Intensiva und Iterativa und ihr Verhältnis zu einander : eine sprachwiszenschaftliche Abhandlung'', 1869 &ndash; Intensiva and Iterativa and their relation to one another. * ''Anthropologische Beiträge'', 1875 &ndash; Anthropological contributions. * ''Immanuel Kant : seine geographischen und anthropologischen Arbeiten'', 1906 &ndash; [[Immanuel Kant]], his geographical and anthropological works. * ''Der Mythus von der Sintflut'', 1912 &ndash; The [[flood myth]].<ref>[https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Gerland,GeorgKarlCornelius,1833-1919.%22&type=author&inst= HathiTrust Digital Library] (published works)</ref>
