{{main|ISO 3166-2}}
'''ISO 3166-2:KI''' is the entry for [[Kiribati]] in [[ISO 3166-2]], part of the [[ISO 3166]] [[standardization|standard]] published by the [[International Organization for Standardization]] (ISO), which defines [[code]]s for the names of the principal [[country subdivision|subdivision]]s (e.g., [[province]]s or [[state (administrative division)|state]]s) of all [[country|countries]] coded in [[ISO 3166-1]].
Currently for Kiribati, ISO 3166-2 codes are defined for [[islands of Kiribati|3 groups of islands (20 inhabited islands)]]. The groups of islands are geographical subdivisions, as the country has no official administrative subdivisions.
Each code consists of two parts, separated by a hyphen. The first part is {{mono|KI}}, the [[ISO 3166-1 alpha-2]] code of Kiribati. The second part is a letter.
==Current codes== Subdivision names are listed as in the ISO 3166-2 standard published by the ISO 3166 Maintenance Agency (ISO 3166/MA).
