{{unref|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox Protected area | name = Mu Ko Ang Thong National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = Ang Thong 1.jpg | photo_caption = Ang Thong National Park from [[Ko Wua Talap]] | map = Thailand | map_caption = Location in Thailand | map_width = | relief = 1 | location = [[Surat Thani Province]], [[Thailand]] | nearest_city = [[Surat Thani]] | coordinates = {{coord|9|37|22|N|99|40|30|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area_km2 = 102 | established = 1980 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = National Park, Wildlife and Plant Conservation Department, Ministry of Natural Resources and Environment | embedded = {{Designation list | embed = yes | designation1 = Ramsar | designation1_date = 14 August 2002 | designation1_number = 1184<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mu Koh Ang Thong Marine National Park|website=[[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] Sites Information Service|url=https://rsis.ramsar.org/ris/1184|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>}} }}
'''Mu Ko Ang Thong''' is a marine [[List of national parks of Thailand|national park]] in the [[Gulf of Thailand]] in [[Surat Thani Province]].<ref name="TAT">{{cite web|title=MU KO ANG THONG NATIONAL PARK|url=https://www.tourismthailand.org/Attraction/Mu-Ko-Ang-Thong-National-Park--5511|website=Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT)|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref> It covers 42 islands in a total area of 102&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, of which about 50&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> are land and the rest is water. The park was established on 12 November 1980.<ref name=DNP>{{cite web|title=Mu Ko Ang Thong National Park|url=http://www.dnp.go.th/parkreserve/asp/style1/default.asp?npid=192&lg=2|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061111031842/http://www.dnp.go.th/parkreserve/asp/style1/default.asp?npid=192&lg=2|dead-url=yes|archive-date=11 November 2006|website=Department of National Parks (DNP)|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref> The northern tip of [[Ko Phaluai]] is also part of the marine park. There is a ranger station, bungalows, a shop, and a restaurant at Ao Phi Beach on [[Ko Wua Talap]].
The name "Ang Thong" (Thai: อ่างทอง) means 'bowl of gold'. "Mu Ko" (หมู่เกาะ) simply means 'group of islands'.
Since 2002 the park has been registered as [[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] site number 1184.<ref name=DNP/>
