{{short description|fictional home of Pippi Longstocking}} {{Infobox fictional location | name = Villa Villekulla | image = File:Villa_Villekulla_and_Pippi.jpg | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = Villa Villekulla, based on the literary texts and original illustrations, at [[Astrid Lindgren's World]] in [[Vimmerby]] | image2 = | image2_size = | alt2 = | caption2 = | source = | alt_name = | country = Sweden | creator = [[Astrid Lindgren]] | ruler = | genre = | type = [[single-family detached home|single-family house]] | ethnic_group = | races = | locations = | people = | population = 1 | first = | last = | blank_label = | blank_data = | blank_label1 = | blank_data1 = | blank_label2 = | blank_data2 = | blank_label3 = | blank_data3 = }} '''Villa Villekulla''' is a [[fiction]]al house that is the home of [[Pippi Longstocking]], a character in a series of books. She lives there with her horse and monkey, [[Mr. Nilsson]]. Outside stands a tree that grows [[Sockerdricka]], a soft drink sold in Sweden.
== 1969 series and 1970 feature films == The house used during the TV series and some films with [[Inger Nilsson]] in the lead role was located in the locality of [[Vibble]] on the island of [[Gotland]] in Sweden. Until the 1970s, the house stood in a garden at the [[Gotland Regiment]] (P 18) south of [[Visby]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Öhrman |first=Roger |title=Vägen till Gotlands historia |series=Gotländskt arkiv, 0434-2429 ; 66(1994):specialvol. |year=1994 |publisher=Gotlands fornsal |location=Visby |isbn=91-88036-13-8 |id={{LIBRIS|7768507}} |page=259 |language=Swedish}}</ref> It was then relocated to Kneippbyn and Kneippbyns Summerland about three kilometers away from where it stood during filming of Pippi Longstocking, where it remains standing to this day. The garden where the filming took place and where Villa Villekulla stood can still be seen. Today there is a [[Scots pine]] growing where it once stood.
