The '''Western Lowlands''' ({{lang-sq|Ultësira Bregdetare or Ultësira Perëndimore}}) is a [[physiogeographical]] region encompassing the western edge of [[Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Udhezimi nr.2 date 20.07.2016|url=http://www.mjedisi.gov.al/files/userfiles/Pyjet/Udhezimi_nr.2_date_20.07.2016.pdf|website=mjedisi.gov.al|page=1|language=Albanian|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Universiteti Shtetëror i Tiranës|title=Buletini i i Universitetit Shteteror te Tiranes|year=1964|page=110|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d0UoAQAAIAAJ&q=Duke+u+bazuar+n%C3%AB+ve%C3%A7orit%C3%AB+gjeologjike,+orografike,+klimatike+dhe+bimore+t%C3%AB+lartp%C3%ABrmendura+t%C3%AB+teritorit,+ne+e+kemi+ndar%C3%AB+k%C3%ABt%C3%AB+t%C3%AB+fundit+n%C3%AB+kat%C3%ABr+nj%C3%ABsi+t%C3%AB+m%C3%ABdha+natyrore:+1)+Alpet+e+Shqip%C3%ABris%C3%AB+s%C3%AB+Veriut;+2)+Krahina+Malore+Q%C3%ABndrore&dq=Duke+u+bazuar+n%C3%AB+ve%C3%A7orit%C3%AB+gjeologjike,+orografike,+klimatike+dhe+bimore+t%C3%AB+lartp%C3%ABrmendura+t%C3%AB+teritorit,+ne+e+kemi+ndar%C3%AB+k%C3%ABt%C3%AB+t%C3%AB+fundit+n%C3%AB+kat%C3%ABr+nj%C3%ABsi+t%C3%AB+m%C3%ABdha+natyrore:+1)+Alpet+e+Shqip%C3%ABris%C3%AB+s%C3%AB+Veriut;+2)+Krahina+Malore+Q%C3%ABndrore&hl=en&ei=xfdQTbzwJ8a_gQfvo7XOCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=book-thumbnail&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ6wEwAA}}</ref> It comprises the flat [[plain]]s extending in the west along the [[Albanian Adriatic Sea Coast|Albanian Adriatic]] and [[Albanian Ionian Sea Coast|Ionian Sea Coast]] that are surrounded by hills and mountains as for instance in the northeast by the [[Albanian Alps]], in the east by the [[Central Mountain Range (Albania)|Skanderbeg Mountains]], in the southeast by the Pindus Mountains and in the southwest by the [[Ceraunian Mountains]]. Nonetheless, the largest and widest plain, measured by area, is the plain of [[Myzeqe]].

