The '''Yangon City Heritage List''' is a list of man-made [[landmarks]] in [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]], so designated by the city government, [[Yangon City Development Committee]].<ref name=mt>{{cite journal | url=http://www.mmtimes.com | title=Special Reports: Heritage List | publisher=The Myanmar Times | date=2001-10-29}}</ref> The list consists of 188 structures (as of 2001), and is largely made up of mostly religious structures and [[British Burma|British colonial era]] buildings. The list is presented by the township in which the structures are located. In 2010, the [[Ministry of Culture (Myanmar)|Ministry of Culture]] further announced that 16 ancient pagodas in [[Yangon Division]] are recognized as cultural heritage sites, effective 10 February 2010. The [[Shwedagon Pagoda]] is recognized as both an Ancient Monument Zone and Protected and Preserved Zone. The other 15 are listed as Ancient Monument Zone.<ref name=mt-2010>{{cite journal | title=Heritage listing for 16 Yangon Div pagodas | work=7-Day News | date=2010-02-18 | language=Burmese}}</ref>
